Module 1: Introduction to Ethical Hacking

Module 1 introduces the basics of Ethical Hacking and cybersecurity. In this module, you will understand what ethical hacking is, why it is important, and how ethical hackers work legally to secure systems. You will learn the difference between ethical hackers and malicious hackers and explore real-world use cases of ethical hacking.

This module also explains the hacking lifecycle, types of hackers, common cyber threats, and the legal rules every ethical hacker must follow. It builds a strong foundation before moving into tools and practical attacks in later modules.

What You Will Learn

What is Ethical Hacking

Types of Hackers (White Hat, Black Hat, Grey Hat)

Why Ethical Hacking is important

Cybersecurity basics and common threats

Ethical hacking phases (Recon, Scan, Exploit, Maintain Access)

Legal & ethical rules (laws, permission, scope)

Outcome

After completing this module, you will clearly understand how ethical hacking works and what mindset is required to continue safely and legally in this field.
